  "text_preview": "\"pancake\" American Sign Language (ASL) ASL Lessons | Bookstore | Library | ASL University Main ► PANCAKE : The American Sign Language (ASL) sign for \"pancake / hotcake / griddlecake / flapjack\" PANCAKE: Memory aid: This sign is looks like you are flipping a pancake. Sample sentence: Do you want pancakes and sausage for breakfast tomorrow? PANCAKE: (variation) Note: There is an initialized version of this sign that uses the tip of the middle finger of the right \"p\" hand to draw a pancake sized circle about a half an inch above the surface of the left flat hand. (I recommend you stick with the pancake flipping version above.) Notes: See: BREAKFAST SAUSAGE WAFFLE * Want to help support ASL University? It's easy : DONATE ( Thanks! ) * Another way to help is to buy something from Dr. Bill's \" B"
